---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Portfolio">
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/portfolio.css">

  <section id="portfolio">
    <Nav currentPath="/portfolio" />

    <div class="portfolio-items">

      <!-- TODO some type of "click to expand" for the preview images -->

      <div class="portfolio-item">
        <h1 class="portfolio-item-heading">
          <div>
            Couetil.com
            <span class="stripe bg-color-purple"></span>
          </div>
        </h1>
        <h2 class="portfolio-item-subheading">
          Personal website built from a public GitHub repo
        </h2>
        <a class="portfolio-item-preview" href="https://github.com/couetilc/couetil.com">
          <img src="/img_couetilcom.jpg">
        </a>
        <ul class="portfolio-item-summary">
          <li>
            Powered by <a href="https://caddyserver.com/">Caddy server</a>
            and generated using
            <a href="https://golang.org/pkg/text/template/">Go templates</a>
            and <a href="https://www.snowpack.dev/">Snowpack</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Deployed
            using <a href="https://docs.docker.com/compose/">Docker Compose</a>
            on a <a href="https://www.digitalocean.com/">Digital Ocean</a> droplet
            alongside an <a href="https://whoisit.couetil.com/couetil.com">analytics service</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Secrets are encrypted with PGP and stored in git using
            <a href="https://github.com/mozilla/sops">Mozilla sops</a>.
          </li>
          <li><a href="https://couetil.com">Website URL</a> and <a href="https://github.com/couetilc/couetil.com">GitHub Repo</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="portfolio-item">
        <h1 class="portfolio-item-heading">
          <div>
            react-social-icons
            <span class="stripe bg-color-pink"></span>
          </div>
        </h1>
        <h2 class="portfolio-item-subheading">
          Co-maintain an Open-Source React.js package on NPM with 10,000+
          weekly downloads
        </h2>
        <a class="portfolio-item-preview" href="https://github.com/couetilc/react-social-icons">
          <img src="/img_reactsocialicons.jpg">
        </a>
        <ul class="portfolio-item-summary">
          <li>Prepared v5 and v6 releases, closing +75 issues and +60 pull requests, accummulating +200 GitHub stars and +20,000 weekly downloads.</li>
          <li>Reduced bundlesize by +95% by transparently implementing code-splitting using Rollup</li>
          <li>Committed to API stability, full coverage testing of API surface and no breaking changes between releases.</li>
          <li>Designed new icons using <a href="https://inkscape.org/">Inkscape</a> and updated documentation for contributors.</li>
          <li>Created CI/CD pipeline with <a href="https://github.com/features/actions">GitHub Actions</a> for testing contributions and publishing releases.</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/couetilc/react-social-icons">GitHub Repo</a> and <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-social-icons">NPM Package</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="portfolio-item">
        <h1 class="portfolio-item-heading">
          <div>
            resume
            <span class="stripe bg-color-yellow"></span>
          </div>
        </h1>
        <h2 class="portfolio-item-subheading">
          My open-source résumé, built using web technologies
        </h2>
        <a class="portfolio-item-preview" href="https://github.com/couetilc/resume">
          <img src="/img_resume.jpg">
        </a>
        <ul class="portfolio-item-summary">
          <li>
            Styled with <a href="https://sass-lang.com/">SASS</a> and uses
            <a href="https://webpack.js.org/">Webpack</a> to compile all
            assets as an HTML bundle. <a href="https://github.com/puppeteer/puppeteer">Puppeteer</a>
            then renders the résumé as a PDF. Convenient container definition using <a href="https://www.docker.com/">Docker</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://github.com/couetilc/resume">GitHub Repo</a> and <a href="https://npmjs.com/package/cc-resume">NPM Package</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="portfolio-item">
        <h1 class="portfolio-item-heading">
          <div>
            caddy-gen
            <span class="stripe bg-color-blue"></span>
          </div>
        </h1>
        <h2 class="portfolio-item-subheading">
          Open-source project using Caddy web server released on DockerHub
          and GitHub
        </h2>
        <a class="portfolio-item-preview" href="https://github.com/couetilc/caddy-gen">
          <img src="/img_caddygen.jpg">
        </a>
        <ul class="portfolio-item-summary">
          <li>
            Proxies requests and pulls TLS certificates for Docker services by
            generating a <a href="https://caddyserver.com/docs/caddyfile">Caddyfile</a>
            using <a href="https://github.com/jwilder/docker-gen">docker-gen</a>
            and <a href="https://golang.org/pkg/text/template/">Go templates</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Pushed features upstream, closing several issues and pull
            requests while adding tests, updating documentation, and fixing
            the <a href="https://www.travis-ci.com/">Travis CI</a> pipeline.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://github.com/couetilc/caddy-gen">GitHub Repo</a> and <a href="https://hub.docker.com/r/couetilc/caddy-gen">DockerHub Repo</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="portfolio-item">
        <h1 class="portfolio-item-heading">
          <div>
            EquineLungExperts.com
            <span class="stripe bg-color-green"></span>
          </div>
        </h1>
        <h2 class="portfolio-item-subheading">
          Designed responsive website enabling clients to request services from
          veterinarians
        </h2>
        <a class="portfolio-item-preview" href="https://equinelungexperts.com">
          <img src="/img_equinelungexperts.jpg">
        </a>
        <ul class="portfolio-item-summary">
          <li>Designed using <a href="https://www.sketch.com/">Sketch</a> and styled with <a href="https://sass-lang.com/">SASS</a>.</li>
          <li>Wrote marketing copy, created logo and other graphics.</li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://nextjs.org/">Next.js</a> powered <a href="https://reactjs.org/">React</a>
            front-end served by <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/cloudfront/">AWS Cloudfront</a>
            with CI/CD using <a href="https://github.com/features/actions">GitHub actions</a>.
          </li>
          <li><a href="https://equinelungexperts.com">Website URL</a> and <a href="https://github.com/couetilc/equine-lung-experts">GitHub Repo</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="portfolio-item">
        <h1 class="portfolio-item-heading">
          <div>
            aws-transcribe-audio
            <span class="stripe bg-color-emerald"></span>
          </div>
        </h1>
        <h2 class="portfolio-item-subheading">
          Open-source software to automatically transcribe audio files added
          to AWS S3 buckets
        </h2>
        <a class="portfolio-item-preview" href="https://github.com/couetilc/aws-transcribe-audio">
          <img src="/img_awstranscribe.jpg">
        </a>
        <ul class="portfolio-item-summary">
          <li>
            Created for a podcast owner who wanted quick, cheap transcripts
            for their episodes.
          </li>
          <li>
            Go binary orchestrating AWS services (S3, Transcribe) targeting AWS
            Lambda runtime using Docker.
          </li>
          <li>
            Thorough documentation and CLI methods organized by
            <a href="https://www.gnu.org/software/make/manual/make.html">Makefile</a>
            to install, update, and remove the project from a specified AWS
            account.
          </li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/couetilc/aws-transcribe-audio">GitHub Repo</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="portfolio-item">
        <h1 class="portfolio-item-heading">
          <div>
            Babblenauts
            <span class="stripe bg-color-orange"></span>
          </div>
        </h1>
        <h2 class="portfolio-item-subheading">
          Winner of "Most Inspirational" Hackathon project at NASA SpaceApps
          2018 in NYC
        </h2>
        <a class="portfolio-item-preview" href="https://2018.spaceappschallenge.org/challenges/universe-beauty-and-wonder/virtual-space-exploration/teams/babblenauts/project">
          <img src="/img_babblenauts.jpg">
        </a>
        <ul class="portfolio-item-summary">
          <li>
            Voice control interface for <a href="https://www.openspaceproject.com/">OpenSpace</a>, an open-source C++ project
            for visualizing the known universe and satellite data.
          </li>
          <li>
            Came up with initial idea, designed React.js front-end for
            controlling the interface, and implemented
            <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Speech_API">Speech Recognition API</a>.
          </li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/couetilc/spaceapps2018">GitHub Repo</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

  </section>
</BaseLayout>
